<REFENTRY ID="baselib-flock-1"> <REFMETA>
<REFENTRYTITLE>flock</REFENTRYTITLE>
<REFMISCINFO>Base Libraries</REFMISCINFO>
</REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>flock</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
apply or remove an advisory lock on an open file.
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<DATE>2 April 2001</DATE>
</REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<SYNOPSIS>
int flock(int fd, int operation)
</SYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<REFSECT1INFO>
<DATE>2 April 2001</DATE>
</REFSECT1INFO>
<TITLE>Description
</TITLE>
<PARA>
The specification for "flock" is as specified in the 4.4BSD-lite but with 
the following differences as listed below.
</PARA>
<PARA>
The following error types are not specified in GNU:
</PARA>
<PARA>
[EBADF]         The argument fd is an invalid descriptor.
</PARA>
<PARA>
[EINVAL]        The argument fd refers to an object other than a file.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>
</REFENTRY>
